<i>The eldest son of our family,
Kim Jung Bong!</i>

9
00:00:51,340 --> 00:00:53,340
<i>It seems that he went to a study room.</i>

10
00:00:58,040 --> 00:01:01,350
<i>[Hyper Olympics
50 won for one game]</i>

11
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:15,840
<i>Next up is my son, who looks
just like me from head to toe...</i>

12
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:20,840
<i>I introduce to you our second son,
Kim Jung Hwan!</i>

13
00:01:22,340 --> 00:01:23,340
<i>Jung Hwan.</i>

14
00:01:23,340 --> 00:01:24,840
<i>Say something for the camera.</i>

15
00:01:25,340 --> 00:01:27,840
<i>Geez... quit doing stuff
like this, already.</i>

16
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,840
<i>Today's the first time
I've done this, though...</i>

17
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:37,340
<i>The only one who I can trust
is my wife.</i>

18
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:43,840
<i>The cornerstone of our home
and my cheetah</i>

19
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:47,340
<i>and my jaguar!
Honey, say something!</i>

20
00:01:51,340 --> 00:01:53,340
Ow!

21
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:56,840
You brought this from
your show again, didn't you?

22
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:57,840
How much is this worth?

23
00:01:58,340 --> 00:02:00,340
980,000 won.

24
00:02:00,340 --> 00:02:02,340
Why? You're such a miser.

25
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:06,340
Is that any way to talk to your husband?

26
00:02:07,340 --> 00:02:10,840
Here... a word to your miser husband?

27
00:02:12,340 --> 00:02:14,840
<i>Geez! I can't even break this...</i>

28
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:18,340
It's not that you won't hit me...
it's that you can't!

29
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:21,340
Shut it, already!

30
00:02:21,340 --> 00:02:23,840
Geez!

31
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:30,840
<i>Excuse, excuse me!</i>

32
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:34,340
<i>Please, excuse me!</i>

33
00:02:34,340 --> 00:02:38,340
<i>Looking, looking
very closely...</i>

34
00:02:38,340 --> 00:02:42,340
<i>is this your home?</i>

35
00:02:42,340 --> 00:02:49,660
<i>Yes, yes, yes it is!
How did you know?</i>

36
00:02:49,660 --> 00:02:52,260
Don't reciprocate his stupidity,
Duk Seon. It'll become a habit.

37
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:54,840
I think it's funny, though.

38
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:58,340
Mom wanted me to bring this to you.
My grandma brought it.

39
00:02:58,340 --> 00:03:01,340
Wow... tell her that we'll enjoy it.

40
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:03,340
Duk Seon, you must be happy.

41
00:03:03,340 --> 00:03:05,340
You really love your grandma.

42
00:03:05,340 --> 00:03:06,340
Yes.

43
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,340
But she's leaving tomorrow.

44
00:03:09,340 --> 00:03:10,340
Hey!

45
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:12,750
Why are you using your hands?
So disgusting...

46
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:14,340
What's it matter to you?

47
00:03:24,340 --> 00:03:27,340
Ah, this scent... you have such a
nice scent coming from you.

48
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:32,340
Geez... don't old farts like me
just smell like old farts?

49
00:03:32,340 --> 00:03:33,340
No.

50
00:03:33,340 --> 00:03:34,840
You smell nice.

51
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,840
Dad smells like this, too.

52
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:44,250
Your belly is so flat, so how did Dad,
my uncle

53
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:47,870
and my chubby aunts
come out of here?

54
00:03:49,340 --> 00:03:54,250
After giving birth
to four chubby kids

55
00:03:54,250 --> 00:03:57,850
my belly ended up shrinking.

56
00:03:57,850 --> 00:04:00,750
Look at the stupid questions she asks,
even though she's a high schooler.

57
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:02,850
Granny. Do you know what
Sung Duk Seon's nickname is?

58
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:04,350
Don't you dare.

59
00:04:04,350 --> 00:04:05,850
It's "IWESS."

60
00:04:05,850 --> 00:04:08,050
It stands for
"Idiots Who Especially Suck at Studying."

61
00:04:08,050 --> 00:04:10,550
As if you're good at studying...
all you do is go to protests!

62
00:04:10,550 --> 00:04:11,640
Did you just call me "you?"

63
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:12,850
You little...

64
00:04:12,850 --> 00:04:15,850
Hey! I'm warning you!

65
00:04:15,850 --> 00:04:20,350
Argue one more time, and I'll beat you
and kick you both out!

66
00:04:20,350 --> 00:04:21,850
I'll beat you to a pulp!

67
00:04:23,350 --> 00:04:27,350
Mother. You're not uncomfortable
in any way, right?

68
00:04:28,850 --> 00:04:31,350
Then, good night.

69
00:04:31,350 --> 00:04:32,350
Okay, okay.

70
00:04:32,350 --> 00:04:33,850
- Go to sleep.
- Yes, Mother.

71
00:04:35,350 --> 00:04:36,350
I'll kill you both...

72
00:04:37,350 --> 00:04:39,850
Sung Duk Seon...
consider yourself saved by Granny.

73
00:04:44,850 --> 00:04:45,850
Granny.

74
00:04:45,850 --> 00:04:46,850
What?

75
00:04:46,850 --> 00:04:49,350
What was Uncle like?
Did he study better than Dad?

76
00:04:49,350 --> 00:04:52,850
No. Your father was a whole lot smarter
than him when it came to school.

77
00:04:52,850 --> 00:04:57,850
And he graduated from
that prestigious school in Gwangju.

78
00:04:59,350 --> 00:05:01,850
Your uncle...

79
00:05:02,850 --> 00:05:08,850
took it upon himself since he was young
to earn money for his younger siblings.

80
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:12,350
But even so, Uncle is the
richest among us.

81
00:05:12,350 --> 00:05:13,350
He even lives in the U.S.

82
00:05:13,350 --> 00:05:17,850
You think that running a laundromat
in the States is prestigious?

83
00:05:17,850 --> 00:05:22,350
He's barely managing
to put food on the table nowadays.

84
00:05:24,350 --> 00:05:26,850
Geez. When I think about your uncle...

85
00:05:27,350 --> 00:05:33,350
my heart just hurts.

86
00:05:34,350 --> 00:05:36,350
Then, who's a better son to you?

87
00:05:36,350 --> 00:05:39,350
Dad calls you every morning.

88
00:05:39,850 --> 00:05:42,350
Why are you asking that?

89
00:05:42,350 --> 00:05:44,850
Both of them are good sons.

90
00:05:46,350 --> 00:05:52,350
Your dad and your uncle never fought.

91
00:05:52,350 --> 00:05:55,850
Why can't you two be like that? Geez.

92
00:05:55,850 --> 00:05:59,850
That's because Bo Ra
always picks fights with me first.

93
00:05:59,850 --> 00:06:00,850
Hey!

94
00:06:00,850 --> 00:06:01,850
- Not again...
- What?

95
00:06:01,850 --> 00:06:03,350
You little...

96
00:06:06,850 --> 00:06:08,350
Come on.

97
00:06:13,850 --> 00:06:18,350
<i>[Episode 2:
One Thing You Misunderstood About Me]</i>

98
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:31,460
<i>[Historic Match Today.]</i>

99
00:06:39,850 --> 00:06:41,850
- Mother, be careful.
- Okay.

100
00:06:41,850 --> 00:06:45,350
At any rate, why are you in
such a rush to leave?

101
00:06:45,350 --> 00:06:49,350
Since you're here, you might as well
spend another night here.

102
00:06:49,350 --> 00:06:56,350
Geez... I have to go home and dry flowers
and a lot of other things.

103
00:06:56,350 --> 00:06:58,850
Granny, I'll come visit
during winter vacation.

104
00:06:58,850 --> 00:07:01,350
Okay, my child.

105
00:07:01,850 --> 00:07:04,850
But... where's Bo Ra?

106
00:07:04,850 --> 00:07:06,850
Where'd she go?

107
00:07:06,850 --> 00:07:10,350
She left early to go to the library.
College students study so much nowadays.

108
00:07:10,350 --> 00:07:13,350
Library, my ass.
She probably went to protest.

109
00:07:13,350 --> 00:07:14,850
Oh dear... hey.

110
00:07:14,850 --> 00:07:16,350
You're throwing this away?

111
00:07:16,850 --> 00:07:17,850
Huh?

112
00:07:17,850 --> 00:07:20,350
Yes.
It's not usable anymore, Mother.

113
00:07:20,350 --> 00:07:22,350
What are you saying?
It looks fine!

114
00:07:22,350 --> 00:07:23,850
Give it here.

115
00:07:23,850 --> 00:07:24,850
Yes, Mother...

116
00:07:24,850 --> 00:07:27,350
Okay. Wow!

117
00:07:27,350 --> 00:07:31,350
I'm going to take this home
and use it.

118
00:07:31,350 --> 00:07:34,350
Geez... you already have
so much stuff to carry back!

119
00:07:34,350 --> 00:07:35,850
Why are you taking that, too?

120
00:07:35,850 --> 00:07:39,350
When I come visit you,
I'll buy you a better one than this!

121
00:07:39,350 --> 00:07:42,350
it's not like you make that much,
so don't be wasting money on me!

122
00:07:42,350 --> 00:07:43,850
I can just use this one.

123
00:07:44,850 --> 00:07:46,840
Hey, you'll be late to work. Go. Quickly!

124
00:07:47,350 --> 00:07:48,350
Geez.

125
00:07:49,350 --> 00:07:51,350
- Good bye!
- Have a safe trip!

126
00:07:51,350 --> 00:07:52,850
I told you, I've got it!

127
00:07:52,850 --> 00:07:54,350
- No!
- Stop it! Sheesh!

128
00:07:54,350 --> 00:07:55,850
- Give me that!
- No, I'm holding it!

129
00:07:55,850 --> 00:07:58,850
- That's mine!
- Stop that!

130
00:07:58,850 --> 00:08:00,850
Stop worrying about me and go!

131
00:08:00,850 --> 00:08:01,850
Give me that!

132
00:08:01,850 --> 00:08:03,350
No! You give me back
my stuff!

133
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:05,350
- Geez!
- Quit it!

134
00:08:05,350 --> 00:08:07,350
Go, already. Go.

135
00:08:07,350 --> 00:08:09,350
So stubborn.

136
00:08:47,350 --> 00:08:48,350
I'm off!

137
00:08:48,350 --> 00:08:49,350
Okay, see you later.

138
00:08:49,850 --> 00:08:52,850
If you wear that and get caught
by your sister, you're dead!

139
00:08:52,850 --> 00:08:55,850
Bo Ra goes drinking every Saturday.
I'll be home before her.

140
00:09:07,350 --> 00:09:09,350
Hey, Kim Jung Hwan! How do I look?

141
00:09:09,350 --> 00:09:10,350
I'm late. Piss off.

142
00:09:15,850 --> 00:09:17,850
Hey, there's only three minutes left.

143
00:09:17,850 --> 00:09:19,850
This is new. How does it look?

144
00:09:19,850 --> 00:09:21,350
Isn't that your sister's?

145
00:09:21,350 --> 00:09:23,350
Hey, only two minutes left!
Let's hurry!

146
00:09:27,350 --> 00:09:28,350
Hello!

147
00:09:32,850 --> 00:09:34,850
Hello, Mister!

148
00:09:35,350 --> 00:09:37,350
Hey! When did you get back?

149
00:09:37,350 --> 00:09:38,350
Yesterday.

150
00:09:38,350 --> 00:09:39,350
Are you going to school?

151
00:09:39,350 --> 00:09:40,350
Yeah.

152
00:09:40,850 --> 00:09:43,350
Drink a lot of milk and
grow big soon, my little Taek!

153
00:09:43,350 --> 00:09:45,350
You have to hurry and grow up
so you can marry me.

154
00:09:45,350 --> 00:09:48,850
- Ow!
- Hey, there's only one minute left!

155
00:09:48,850 --> 00:09:49,850
You want to die?

156
00:09:50,350 --> 00:09:51,850
You want to die? Hey!

157
00:09:58,350 --> 00:10:00,350
Be on time for a change.

158
00:10:00,350 --> 00:10:03,850
Aren't you tired of getting punished
for being late every morning?

159
00:10:04,850 --> 00:10:07,350
It doesn't matter.
My head is full of rocks, anyway.

160
00:10:08,350 --> 00:10:11,850
Hey, Wang Ja Hyun.
So... what'd you get?

161
00:10:11,850 --> 00:10:14,350
Only 45 percent.

162
00:10:14,350 --> 00:10:16,350
I don't think our love
will work out.

163
00:10:16,350 --> 00:10:17,350
Look.

164
00:10:18,350 --> 00:10:20,850
You idiot... you did it wrong!

165
00:10:20,850 --> 00:10:21,850
What?

166
00:10:21,850 --> 00:10:26,350
You wrote your name first.
That means you only like him 45 percent.

167
00:10:26,350 --> 00:10:27,350
Really?

168
00:10:27,350 --> 00:10:28,350
Let me try it again.

169
00:10:29,350 --> 00:10:31,350
I'll write his name first.

170
00:10:45,350 --> 00:10:46,350
70 percent!

171
00:10:46,350 --> 00:10:47,350
70 percent?

172
00:10:47,350 --> 00:10:50,850
70 percent? Byun likes you 70 percent?

173
00:10:50,850 --> 00:10:51,850
As if.

174
00:10:51,850 --> 00:10:53,850
I'm going to try it, too. Me too.

175
00:11:04,350 --> 00:11:05,350
What is this?

176
00:11:05,350 --> 00:11:06,850
They're not Korean noodles...

177
00:11:06,850 --> 00:11:08,350
It's called spaghetti.

178
00:11:08,350 --> 00:11:09,850
You've never had it, right?

179
00:11:09,850 --> 00:11:11,850
It's the first time I've seen it.

180
00:11:11,850 --> 00:11:14,350
You should have just made
normal noodles.

181
00:11:14,350 --> 00:11:16,350
I have money, so might as well spend it.

182
00:11:16,350 --> 00:11:18,350
I'm going to eat what
rich people eat before I die.

183
00:11:18,350 --> 00:11:19,850
What are you doing?

184
00:11:19,850 --> 00:11:21,350
Are you boiling Korean noodles?

185
00:11:21,350 --> 00:11:22,850
Are these chewy noodles?

186
00:11:22,850 --> 00:11:24,350
I said it's spaghetti!

187
00:11:25,350 --> 00:11:26,350
Okay.

188
00:11:26,350 --> 00:11:29,350
Stop glaring like that.
You look so scary.

189
00:11:29,350 --> 00:11:34,350
At any rate, why are we celebrating
Taek's victory at our place?

190
00:11:34,350 --> 00:11:36,950
It's just the two of them,
so it's not like they'll cook anything.

191
00:11:36,950 --> 00:11:38,250
I told them to just buy chicken.

192
00:11:38,250 --> 00:11:39,850
- Taek is coming, too.
- Oh, really?

193
00:11:39,850 --> 00:11:42,850
I guess I'll see Mr. Choi
for the first time in a while, huh?

194
00:11:43,350 --> 00:11:46,350
Wouldn't it be great if I had a daughter
and got him as a son-in-law?

195
00:11:46,350 --> 00:11:47,850
I claimed Taek first.

196
00:11:47,850 --> 00:11:49,350
He's going to be my son-in-law.

197
00:11:50,350 --> 00:11:53,350
But, Bo Ra isn't coming today?
Everyone else is.

198
00:11:53,850 --> 00:11:57,350
She does something at school
every Saturday and comes home late.

199
00:11:57,350 --> 00:11:59,350
She won't be home after
12:00 a.m. today, either.

200
00:11:59,350 --> 00:12:02,350
Mom! Where are you?

201
00:12:02,350 --> 00:12:04,350
Bo Ra?

202
00:12:04,350 --> 00:12:07,850
What the heck?
Why is she back so early?

203
00:12:07,850 --> 00:12:09,350
Mom!

204
00:12:11,350 --> 00:12:17,850
Eight, nine, ten, eleven, twelve,
thirteen, fourteen, fifteen, sixteen...

205
00:12:17,850 --> 00:12:19,350
How old am I, again?

206
00:12:19,350 --> 00:12:20,850
Eighteen.

207
00:12:20,850 --> 00:12:22,350
Click it two more times.

208
00:12:22,350 --> 00:12:24,850
Seventeen, eighteen.

209
00:12:29,350 --> 00:12:30,850
If it breaks, your love is doomed.

210
00:12:30,850 --> 00:12:33,350
If it breaks, your love won't come true.

211
00:12:33,350 --> 00:12:37,850
Hey. Don't you even dream
of love until you get those braces off.

212
00:12:39,850 --> 00:12:40,850
Shush.

213
00:12:41,350 --> 00:12:43,350
My first love depends on this.

214
00:12:44,350 --> 00:12:46,350
I'm going to a club trip today.

215
00:12:47,350 --> 00:12:49,350
I'm going to go as soon as I pack my bag.

216
00:12:54,850 --> 00:12:56,850
What's this about a club trip,
all of the sudden?

217
00:12:57,850 --> 00:12:59,350
I don't know.

218
00:12:59,350 --> 00:13:02,850
An upperclassman said he got
paid today, so he wants to go Daesungri.

219
00:13:02,850 --> 00:13:05,350
Crazy bastard!
He just does whatever he wants!

220
00:13:07,350 --> 00:13:08,350
Mom.

221
00:13:08,350 --> 00:13:13,350
Did you see my tan pants
that were here?

222
00:13:14,350 --> 00:13:16,850
I washed those this morning
and hung them up.

223
00:13:16,850 --> 00:13:18,750
They should be dry by now.
Let me go get them.

224
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:21,350
No, it's okay.
I'll just wear these pants.

225
00:13:24,850 --> 00:13:26,350
But Mom...

226
00:13:26,350 --> 00:13:28,350
I don't see that.

227
00:13:28,850 --> 00:13:30,850
You know... my jacket.

228
00:13:32,350 --> 00:13:33,850
Where's my jacket?

229
00:13:35,350 --> 00:13:36,850
The baseball jacket.

230
00:13:39,350 --> 00:13:41,850
I left that at the dry cleaner's...

231
00:13:41,850 --> 00:13:43,850
No, no. My denim jacket.

232
00:13:46,850 --> 00:13:47,850
Huh?

233
00:13:47,850 --> 00:13:49,350
Where's my denim jacket?

234
00:13:49,850 --> 00:13:51,850
It was definitely here.

235
00:13:51,850 --> 00:13:53,350
I even saw it this morning!

236
00:13:55,350 --> 00:13:57,350
Where's my denim jacket?

237
00:13:57,350 --> 00:13:58,350
Huh?

238
00:13:58,350 --> 00:14:00,350
Um... that is...

239
00:14:00,350 --> 00:14:01,850
um... Bo Ra.

240
00:14:01,850 --> 00:14:03,350
It was definitely here
this morning!

241
00:14:03,350 --> 00:14:06,350
Why isn't it here now?

242
00:14:06,350 --> 00:14:08,350
Where's my denim jacket?

243
00:14:08,350 --> 00:14:12,850
Damn it! Hmm... did I wash it?

244
00:14:12,850 --> 00:14:14,350
Wait just a minute.

245
00:14:15,850 --> 00:14:17,850
Where's my denim jacket?

246
00:14:17,850 --> 00:14:19,350
Damn it!

247
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:22,850
<i>Sung Duk Seon! I'll kill her!</i>

248
00:14:32,350 --> 00:14:34,350
<i>I'm going to kill her!</i>

249
00:14:34,350 --> 00:14:35,850
<i>Damn Sung Duk Seon!</i>

250
00:14:35,850 --> 00:14:38,850
I think watching the fiasco downstairs
would be more entertaining than this.

251
00:14:39,350 --> 00:14:42,350
Ma'am. Lend me your phone.
Oh, and the phone book.

252
00:14:52,350 --> 00:14:54,350
<i>Yes, this is Ssangmundong High School.</i>

253
00:14:54,350 --> 00:14:56,850
Sir! No, no...

254
00:14:56,850 --> 00:14:58,350
Can you put a the dean
on the line?

255
00:15:00,850 --> 00:15:02,850
Yes, this is the dean.

256
00:15:02,850 --> 00:15:04,350
Dong Ryong's father!

257
00:15:04,350 --> 00:15:05,850
Can you put No Eul on the line?

258
00:15:07,850 --> 00:15:09,350
Yes, hello?

259
00:15:09,850 --> 00:15:10,850
Mom?

260
00:15:37,850 --> 00:15:38,850
Duk Seon!

261
00:15:42,350 --> 00:15:45,350
Duk Seon! Jacket!

262
00:16:12,850 --> 00:16:15,350
<i>[Dae Wang Computer Game Cafe]</i>

263
00:16:49,840 --> 00:16:52,340
He's definitely on steroids. For sure.

264
00:17:04,340 --> 00:17:06,340
<i>What the hell am I going to wear?</i>

265
00:17:06,340 --> 00:17:09,340
<i>I'm going to kill Sung Duk Seon!
Damn it!</i>

266
00:17:09,340 --> 00:17:11,340
<i>Where did Sung Duk Seon go?</i>

267
00:17:11,340 --> 00:17:15,340
Geez... where do you think?
School, obviously.

268
00:17:15,340 --> 00:17:18,840
Geez... sometimes, I wonder how
she even got into Seoul University.

269
00:17:19,340 --> 00:17:20,840
She's coming. Over there.

270
00:18:02,340 --> 00:18:03,840
Where are you going?

271
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:04,840
To go kill Sung Duk Seon.

272
00:18:04,840 --> 00:18:05,840
Here it is!

273
00:18:10,340 --> 00:18:12,340
It was right here.

274
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:14,340
I totally forgot.

275
00:18:19,340 --> 00:18:21,340
I'm back from school.

276
00:18:21,340 --> 00:18:22,840
Oh, you're home, Duk Seon?

277
00:18:22,840 --> 00:18:24,340
You're early today.

278
00:18:25,340 --> 00:18:28,340
It's Saturday so I got out earlier.

279
00:18:28,340 --> 00:18:30,340
Hey, Sung Duk Seon.

280
00:18:30,340 --> 00:18:31,340
What?

281
00:18:32,340 --> 00:18:34,340
Did you wear your indoor slippers
to school today?

282
00:18:35,340 --> 00:18:38,230
Yeah. Duh.

283
00:18:40,340 --> 00:18:41,840
Duk Seon.

284
00:18:41,840 --> 00:18:43,750
Go get washed up,
and let's go to Jung Hwan's.

285
00:18:43,750 --> 00:18:45,840
We're celebrating Taek's victory today.

286
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:48,340
So Jung Hwan's mom bought
American noodles and everything.

287
00:18:48,340 --> 00:18:49,840
Damn it!

288
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:52,340
What are you going to do about this?

289
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:56,340
- Should I use the hair dryer?
- I don't have time for that!

290
00:18:56,340 --> 00:18:58,340
Why did you wash this
without even asking me?

291
00:18:58,340 --> 00:19:01,340
What am I supposed to wear today?

292
00:19:01,340 --> 00:19:04,340
Hey. Grow up.

293
00:19:04,340 --> 00:19:05,840
What did you just say to me?

294
00:19:05,840 --> 00:19:08,340
I said, grow up instead
of harassing Mom!

295
00:19:08,340 --> 00:19:09,340
You little... hey!

296
00:19:09,340 --> 00:19:11,340
You grow up.

297
00:19:11,340 --> 00:19:12,340
You're always last place.

298
00:19:12,340 --> 00:19:15,340
I'm not last place!
There are other people lower than me!

299
00:19:15,340 --> 00:19:16,840
Is that something to brag about?

300
00:19:16,840 --> 00:19:19,650
And also, what do you need clothes for
when all you do is play all day?

301
00:19:19,650 --> 00:19:21,340
Just wear whatever!

302
00:19:21,340 --> 00:19:24,040
You're ugly, so it's not like
you need to worry about looks anyway.

303
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:25,040
I held back a lot today.

304
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:26,840
You're dead today. Hey!

305
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:28,340
You think you're pretty?

306
00:19:28,340 --> 00:19:29,840
You nose looks like a man's!

307
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:31,340
Damn it!

308
00:19:31,340 --> 00:19:33,840
I'm back... off to school.

309
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:37,840
Am I your friend? Huh?

310
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:39,540
I'm going to kill you!
You drive me crazy!

311
00:19:39,540 --> 00:19:41,840
"You?" I'll kill you!

312
00:19:41,840 --> 00:19:43,840
Crazy bitch!

313
00:19:54,540 --> 00:19:58,340
<i>[A moment's decision influences
the next 10 years of your life.]</i>

314
00:20:24,840 --> 00:20:28,840
If I met Mr. Young Pil,
my life would be complete!

315
00:20:29,340 --> 00:20:33,840
Jo Young Pil is two years younger
than you! No need call him "Mr."

316
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:36,340
Even so...

317
00:20:37,340 --> 00:20:40,840
Hi! What are you all up to?

318
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:43,340
- They're still not here?
- Oh, hi, Jin Joo!

319
00:20:43,340 --> 00:20:46,340
Wow, look at everyone!

320
00:20:47,340 --> 00:20:48,840
Honey, you're home early today.

321
00:20:48,840 --> 00:20:49,840
Geez, you...

322
00:20:49,840 --> 00:20:52,650
Mr. Choi's dad said that he's treating us
for the first time in a while

323
00:20:52,650 --> 00:20:54,750
so of course I couldn't be late
on a day like today.

324
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:56,840
Speaking of which,
what's on the menu for today?

325
00:20:56,840 --> 00:20:58,340
We have spaghetti.

326
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:00,840
Get... getty?
What's that?

327
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:03,340
Spaghetti. It's American food.

328
00:21:03,340 --> 00:21:05,840
How are we supposed to eat this, anyway?

329
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:08,340
How do you think?
The same way you eat anything else.

330
00:21:08,840 --> 00:21:11,340
Why isn't Mr. Choi here yet?
The noodles are getting bloated.

331
00:21:11,340 --> 00:21:13,840
Mr. Choi is like the Jo Young Pil
of our neighborhood.

332
00:21:13,840 --> 00:21:16,340
The superstar always comes last.

333
00:21:18,340 --> 00:21:20,340
Oh, the superstar is here.

334
00:21:20,340 --> 00:21:22,340
The door is open,
so why is he using the bell?

335
00:21:22,340 --> 00:21:24,340
Here you go.

336
00:21:24,840 --> 00:21:26,340
Hello.

337
00:21:26,950 --> 00:21:28,340
"Kantapia."

338
00:21:28,340 --> 00:21:29,840
Go to Jung Bong's room.

339
00:21:30,340 --> 00:21:32,340
Why did you get here so late?

340
00:21:32,340 --> 00:21:34,340
We were waiting for you.

341
00:21:34,340 --> 00:21:36,840
You should have closed shop
on a day like today.

342
00:21:36,840 --> 00:21:39,450
You don't need to work so hard
when your son earns so much money.

343
00:21:39,450 --> 00:21:42,340
That's not my money.
That's Taek's.

344
00:21:42,340 --> 00:21:44,840
Where would Taek even use that money?

345
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:47,340
Why not use some of it?

346
00:21:47,340 --> 00:21:48,340
Oh yes... here you go.

347
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:52,340
Wow... you bought two of them?

348
00:21:52,340 --> 00:21:54,340
Honey. Put this in Jung Hwan's room.

349
00:21:54,340 --> 00:21:55,340
Okay.

350
00:21:57,840 --> 00:21:59,340
Is Taek coming, too?

351
00:21:59,340 --> 00:22:00,840
It's been so long since
I've seen him.

352
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:02,340
He's coming.

353
00:22:03,340 --> 00:22:04,540
He doesn't even attend school

354
00:22:04,540 --> 00:22:07,340
so the only friends he has
are the kids from this block.

355
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:09,840
But he wants to cool his head first.

356
00:22:12,840 --> 00:22:13,840
<i>Oh, geez.</i>

357
00:22:15,840 --> 00:22:16,840
<i>Mr. Choi.</i>

358
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:18,340
<i>Say a greeting for me.</i>

359
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:21,340
<i>- Huh?
- What's that?</i>

360
00:22:22,340 --> 00:22:23,340
<i>Mr. Choi!</i>

361
00:22:23,340 --> 00:22:25,340
<i>Please grant this wish of mine!</i>

362
00:22:25,340 --> 00:22:26,340
<i>No, it's okay.</i>

363
00:22:26,840 --> 00:22:28,340
<i>Geez... then...</i>

364
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:30,840
<i>Bo Ra's dad,
please say something!</i>

365
00:22:33,340 --> 00:22:36,840
<i>Then, what about the Ugly Sisters
of our town?</i>

366
00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:38,340
<i>- A camera!
- So amazing!</i>

367
00:22:38,340 --> 00:22:39,840
<i>It records our movements!</i>

368
00:22:39,840 --> 00:22:40,840
<i>Geez.</i>

369
00:22:40,840 --> 00:22:41,840
<i>Oh!</i>

370
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:44,340
<i>There's a missing lady here.</i>

371
00:22:44,340 --> 00:22:46,840
<i>There was a lady who was
the prettiest among you three.</i>

372
00:22:47,340 --> 00:22:49,840
<i>Has anyone seen my cheetah?</i>

373
00:22:51,340 --> 00:22:52,840
<i>Here she is.</i>

374
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:54,540
<i>I'm giving you until the count of three.</i>

375
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:55,840
<i>One, two, three!</i>

376
00:22:56,840 --> 00:22:59,340
You thought I was putting it down,
right?

377
00:22:59,340 --> 00:23:00,340
- Geez...
- Ow!

378
00:23:00,340 --> 00:23:01,340
Get rid of it!

379
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:06,840
My eye almost popped out! What
would I do if that happened?

380
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:10,840
- I'm back.
- Hello.

381
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:11,840
Hey there.

382
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:14,340
- Where's our Sun Woo?
- He's coming.

383
00:23:14,840 --> 00:23:18,840
- Hello! I'm back from school!
- You're here, my son?

384
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:21,840
Our Sun Woo... you know that
I brag about you, right?

385
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:22,840
Yes.

386
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:26,840
I wonder why my friend
isn't coming?

387
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:27,840
Who?

388
00:23:29,340 --> 00:23:33,340
Oh, President Sung!

389
00:23:33,340 --> 00:23:36,840
Oh, President Kim!

390
00:23:36,840 --> 00:23:42,340
- It's so great to see you!
- It's so great to see you!

391
00:23:42,340 --> 00:23:44,340
Oh, Duk Seon!

392
00:23:44,340 --> 00:23:47,340
Thanks for reciprocating.

393
00:23:47,340 --> 00:23:51,340
I got it. I know.

394
00:23:52,840 --> 00:23:54,840
What the hell are you two doing?

395
00:23:54,840 --> 00:23:56,840
How come Taek didn't come with you?

396
00:23:56,840 --> 00:23:57,840
He's coming.

397
00:23:57,840 --> 00:24:00,840
The star of the show
always shows up last!

398
00:24:00,840 --> 00:24:02,840
I told him to go borrow some comic books.

399
00:24:03,340 --> 00:24:05,840
Wow, Duk Seon.
You've got some nerve.

400
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:09,340
Making the Almighty Taek
do that for you?

401
00:24:09,340 --> 00:24:11,340
Only outsiders care about that stuff.

402
00:24:11,340 --> 00:24:13,840
Do you think the kids
treat him any differently?

403
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:16,340
They're childhood friends.

404
00:24:19,340 --> 00:24:20,840
Hello.

405
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:23,840
- Congratulations!
- Yay!

406
00:24:23,840 --> 00:24:25,840
- Come on in!
- Hi!

407
00:24:26,340 --> 00:24:29,340
Thank you for gracing us with
your presence today, sir.

408
00:24:30,340 --> 00:24:33,340
This place is unfit for your presence,
and yet you've come.

409
00:24:33,340 --> 00:24:35,840
What an honor this is.

410
00:24:36,340 --> 00:24:40,340
Oh yeah, I want you all to greet him.
He's our son-in-law.

411
00:24:40,340 --> 00:24:44,340
What are you saying?
He's going to marry my Jin Joo!

412
00:24:44,340 --> 00:24:46,340
We called dibs first! Right, Taek?

413
00:24:48,840 --> 00:24:50,840
Welcome. I'm your new mother.

414
00:24:50,840 --> 00:24:52,340
I'm your new father.

415
00:24:54,340 --> 00:24:56,340
Oh, stop it, already.

416
00:24:56,340 --> 00:24:58,340
Go inside.
All the kids are here.

417
00:24:58,340 --> 00:24:59,340
Enjoy your meal.

418
00:24:59,340 --> 00:25:00,340
Okay.

419
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:03,340
Look at him.
He's all grown now.

420
00:25:03,340 --> 00:25:07,340
Geez... he's totally like an adult!

421
00:25:07,340 --> 00:25:11,340
Compared to our kids,
he seems so much older!

422
00:25:11,840 --> 00:25:13,840
He's still just a kid.

423
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:15,340
All he knows how to do
is play Baduk.

424
00:25:15,340 --> 00:25:17,340
He knows nothing about the world.

425
00:25:17,340 --> 00:25:22,340
Geez, you... elements of the real
world are all a part of Baduk.

426
00:25:22,340 --> 00:25:24,340
Do you think Taek doesn't know that?

427
00:25:24,340 --> 00:25:27,340
And he's one of the
best Baduk players ever.

428
00:25:27,340 --> 00:25:30,840
In some ways, he might know more about
the world than we adults do.

429
00:25:31,340 --> 00:25:35,340
Speaking of which, how much was
the prize money this time around?

430
00:25:35,340 --> 00:25:37,840
I heard that he won the largest
competition in all of Korea.

431
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:41,930
50,000,000 won.

432
00:25:45,340 --> 00:25:47,340
Oh my goodness!

433
00:25:47,340 --> 00:25:50,840
Taek should buy a huge round
for the kids today!

434
00:25:50,840 --> 00:25:53,340
Oh my God...
50,000,000 won...

435
00:25:53,340 --> 00:25:55,340
I'm speechless.

436
00:25:55,340 --> 00:25:57,840
- That's so much money.
- You must be so happy. I'm so jealous.

437
00:25:57,840 --> 00:25:59,250
- 50,000,000 won?
- 50,000,000 won?

438
00:26:02,340 --> 00:26:04,340
Buy us ddukbokki.

439
00:26:04,340 --> 00:26:14,340
- Ddukbokki!
- Ddukbokki!

440
00:26:14,340 --> 00:26:16,840
- Hey, have some chicken.
- That's okay.

441
00:26:17,340 --> 00:26:21,840
Look at how pale your face is. Don't
forget to work out once in a while.

442
00:26:22,340 --> 00:26:25,340
Is this your stomach or your back?
You're so thin.

443
00:26:25,340 --> 00:26:26,340
I'm fine.

444
00:26:26,340 --> 00:26:28,250
Hey, Taek. You're going to China again,
right?

445
00:26:28,250 --> 00:26:30,950
When are you coming back?
Are you coming back before your birthday?

446
00:26:30,950 --> 00:26:32,000
Why?

447
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:34,750
- You want to throw him a birthday party?
- No. Bring us some liquor.

448
00:26:34,750 --> 00:26:37,840
- Mom!
- What's wrong with you?

449
00:26:37,840 --> 00:26:40,040
Why are you telling Taek to do that?
Buy it yourselves!

450
00:26:40,040 --> 00:26:41,840
He's on a different level.

451
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:44,340
They always give him expensive
bottles of liquor in China.

452
00:26:44,340 --> 00:26:45,340
Hey, Choi Taek.

453
00:26:45,340 --> 00:26:48,340
Don't give it to your dad this time.
Give it to us. Okay?

454
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:52,840
- Hey.
- Where are you going?

455
00:26:52,840 --> 00:26:56,210
- To get some juice.
- Don't you dare tell on us.

456
00:26:56,210 --> 00:26:57,840
Fine.

457
00:26:57,840 --> 00:26:59,840
Hey, ugly.

458
00:26:59,840 --> 00:27:01,340
Get only the juice, all right?

459
00:27:01,340 --> 00:27:04,340
Don't eat the sausage in the fridge.
It's Jung Bong's.

460
00:27:04,340 --> 00:27:05,840
I won't!

461
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:09,840
Land.

462
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:10,840
Land is the best.

463
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:12,840
Mr. Choi, buy some land no matter what.

464
00:27:12,840 --> 00:27:15,450
They say that the value of the land
in Ilsan is rising nowadays.

465
00:27:15,450 --> 00:27:17,340
Geez... if you don't know anything,
don't talk.

466
00:27:17,340 --> 00:27:20,340
What's there to see in Ilsan?
It's in the middle of nowhere!

467
00:27:20,340 --> 00:27:25,340
Rather, it's safest to put
your money in a bank.

468
00:27:25,340 --> 00:27:28,340
Geez... bank interest
doesn't even amount to much.

469
00:27:28,340 --> 00:27:31,840
Of course, the interest rates
have decreased a bit

470
00:27:31,840 --> 00:27:36,340
so it'll only be about 15 percent or so
but even so, you'll accrue interest.

471
00:27:36,340 --> 00:27:37,840
There's no place safer than a bank.

472
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:42,340
You're going to put
all that money in a bank?

473
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:44,340
Mr. Choi.

474
00:27:44,340 --> 00:27:47,340
Buy an apartment.
A great one, in Gangnam.

475
00:27:47,340 --> 00:27:50,560
Um... what's it called?
Umma (Mom) Apartment, yes.

476
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:52,190
It's Eunma...

477
00:27:52,190 --> 00:27:53,340
Yeah. Umma. Umma Apartment.

478
00:27:53,340 --> 00:27:57,340
- Eunma. Eunma.
- That's what I just said! Umma. Umma.

479
00:27:57,340 --> 00:27:59,340
I heard they go for 50,000,000 won.

480
00:28:00,340 --> 00:28:03,340
What? How is an apartment
that much money?

481
00:28:15,840 --> 00:28:17,340
Where is it?

482
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:26,340
- Anyway, congratulations, Mr. Choi!
- Yes. Thank you.

483
00:28:26,340 --> 00:28:30,340
Meanwhile, our daughters
are busy blowing our money...

484
00:28:30,340 --> 00:28:33,340
Mr. Choi is so lucky.

485
00:28:33,840 --> 00:28:36,840
Mr. Kim, come sit down.
It's still not working?

486
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:42,340
Geez... you paid so much for it
but you don't know how to use it?

487
00:28:42,340 --> 00:28:44,840
If it doesn't work, just give up
and come sit here!

488
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:48,340
Why are you fussing about putting on
some music in the middle of the day?

489
00:28:48,340 --> 00:28:51,840
Then, let's just toast! Cheers!

490
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:54,340
Congratulations!

491
00:28:54,340 --> 00:28:55,840
Thank you.

492
00:29:10,890 --> 00:29:12,160
Jin Joo.

493
00:29:13,840 --> 00:29:16,340
Does that taste good?

494
00:29:16,340 --> 00:29:17,840
Can you give me just a bite?

495
00:29:23,840 --> 00:29:25,340
Here, here, here!

496
00:29:25,340 --> 00:29:27,340
Here it is!

497
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:35,840
Who could that be?

498
00:29:37,840 --> 00:29:38,840
Who could that be?

499
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:41,170
I think someone's here.

500
00:29:42,440 --> 00:29:43,440
Mr. Choi.

501
00:29:43,440 --> 00:29:45,440
What did I say before?

502
00:29:45,440 --> 00:29:46,440
Excuse me?

503
00:29:46,940 --> 00:29:49,440
What did I tell you to buy
if you got a lot of money?

504
