1017
01:12:53,170 --> 01:12:54,670
Mister.

1018
01:12:57,670 --> 01:12:59,670
I heard that your mother passed away.

1019
01:13:02,670 --> 01:13:04,170
I'm sorry.

1020
01:13:05,170 --> 01:13:06,670
I couldn't even visit.

1021
01:13:08,170 --> 01:13:11,670
Why are you bringing that up?

1022
01:13:11,670 --> 01:13:14,170
I'm going to start crying.

1023
01:13:16,670 --> 01:13:19,170
That's right.

1024
01:13:19,170 --> 01:13:25,170
Mothers tend to be the one you miss
the most, whether they're alive or dead.

1025
01:13:26,670 --> 01:13:29,170
Oh yeah... I even got to see
my older brother.

1026
01:13:35,670 --> 01:13:37,170
Taek.

1027
01:13:38,170 --> 01:13:42,130
When do you miss
your mother most?

1028
01:13:46,670 --> 01:13:47,670
Hmm?

1029
01:13:58,170 --> 01:14:00,170
Every day.

1030
01:14:04,670 --> 01:14:08,670
I miss my mom every single day.

1031
01:14:26,170 --> 01:14:29,670
<i>An adult-like child is just one
without complaints.</i>

1032
01:14:31,170 --> 01:14:34,670
<i>It's just that they've acclimated
to the world of adults</i>

1033
01:14:34,670 --> 01:14:38,170
<i>and they've grown used to
the illusions around them.</i>

1034
01:14:39,670 --> 01:14:43,170
<i>An adult-like child
is just that, a child.</i>

1035
01:14:48,170 --> 01:14:50,670
<i>An illusion is short,
but a misunderstanding lasts a long time.</i>

1036
01:14:50,670 --> 01:14:55,170
<i>That's why illusions offer freedom while
misunderstandings chain you down.</i>

1037
01:15:25,170 --> 01:15:28,670
<i>Happy birthday to you,
happy birthday to you!</i>

1038
01:15:28,670 --> 01:15:31,170
<i>Happy birthday, dear Taek!</i>

1039
01:15:31,170 --> 01:15:33,670
<i>Happy birthday to you!</i>

1040
01:15:35,170 --> 01:15:37,170
Yay!

1041
01:15:38,670 --> 01:15:41,170
Come home earlier! Sheesh.

1042
01:15:41,170 --> 01:15:42,670
Look here.

1043
01:15:43,170 --> 01:15:45,170
Hey, change into something else.
Are you a grandpa?

1044
01:15:45,170 --> 01:15:47,070
I thought I'd die of starvation
waiting for you.

1045
01:15:47,070 --> 01:15:48,170
We even called you!

1046
01:15:48,170 --> 01:15:49,170
Hurry up and blow it out.

1047
01:15:49,170 --> 01:15:50,370
It's going to blow out.
Hurry.

1048
01:15:50,370 --> 01:15:52,170
Hurry! One, two, three!

1049
01:15:54,170 --> 01:15:58,170
- Here, your present.
- Yay!

1050
01:15:58,170 --> 01:15:59,170
<i>[Jeon In Kwon]</i>

1051
01:15:59,170 --> 01:16:00,170
We're done now, right?

1052
01:16:00,170 --> 01:16:02,170
Where is it, huh? Hurry it up.

1053
01:16:02,170 --> 01:16:03,370
- Where is it?
- Take it out!

1054
01:16:03,370 --> 01:16:04,670
Here, here.

1055
01:16:04,670 --> 01:16:07,170
Hey, let's do this later.
Where is it?

1056
01:16:07,170 --> 01:16:09,670
Let's watch TV.

1057
01:16:09,670 --> 01:16:11,170
Hurry up and take it out!

1058
01:16:12,170 --> 01:16:13,670
Hey, let me see.

1059
01:16:13,670 --> 01:16:15,670
Where is it? Hey, lower the volume!

1060
01:16:15,670 --> 01:16:18,270
Taek, you're not going to eat
all this, right? I'm taking it home!

1061
01:16:18,270 --> 01:16:19,270
- Okay?
- Where is it?

1062
01:16:19,270 --> 01:16:21,170
Hey, it's obviously in his bag!
Geez!

1063
01:16:21,170 --> 01:16:22,170
Bag! Give me that.

1064
01:16:22,170 --> 01:16:24,170
Let me see. Open it.

1065
01:16:24,170 --> 01:16:26,170
All right, all right, all right!

1066
01:16:27,670 --> 01:16:29,670
It's a good one! Nice job!

1067
01:16:29,670 --> 01:16:32,170
Mom! These kids are drinking!

1068
01:16:32,170 --> 01:16:34,170
Stop screaming! Hey!

1069
01:16:36,170 --> 01:16:37,170
Ow!

1070
01:16:37,170 --> 01:16:39,170
They're drinking!

1071
01:16:39,170 --> 01:16:42,670
<i>Taek was the last one to move here.</i>

1072
01:17:19,170 --> 01:17:21,670
<i>After his mother passed away,
they left</i>

1073
01:17:21,670 --> 01:17:24,670
<i>her hometown which was
full of her scent and came to Seoul.</i>

1074
01:17:27,170 --> 01:17:31,670
<i>We don't know why this father and son
chose this block in particular</i>

1075
01:17:31,670 --> 01:17:32,750
<i>but what I am sure of</i>

1076
01:17:32,780 --> 01:17:38,670
<i>is that the four troublemakers of
this block found a new friend.</i>

1077
01:18:12,670 --> 01:18:15,670
<i>Taek was a quiet kid.</i>

1078
01:18:16,170 --> 01:18:22,170
<i>So the boisterous kids on this block
may have been too much for him.</i>

1079
01:19:38,170 --> 01:19:41,670
<i>Even so, Taek was always with us.</i>

1080
01:19:42,170 --> 01:19:44,670
<i>Even when we were
doing mischievous things</i>

1081
01:19:44,670 --> 01:19:48,170
<i>or doing pathetic things
he was always by our side.</i>

1082
01:19:49,170 --> 01:19:52,670
<i>Of course, he always had
an expressionless face.</i>

1083
01:19:52,670 --> 01:19:55,170
<i>But even so, he was with us.</i>

1084
01:20:02,170 --> 01:20:07,170
<i>Still, the block creates friendships
just through the power of time.</i>

1085
01:20:07,670 --> 01:20:12,670
<i>That is how the taciturn child
and the four noisy kids became friends.</i>

1086
01:20:12,670 --> 01:20:16,170
<i>And that's how we became five.</i>

1087
01:20:34,170 --> 01:20:36,170
Geez... really.

1088
01:20:38,170 --> 01:20:39,670
Just from drinking this?

1089
01:20:39,670 --> 01:20:42,170
And here, I thought you guys
could handle your liquor.

1090
01:20:47,170 --> 01:20:48,170
Hey.

1091
01:20:48,670 --> 01:20:51,670
Just try it, then. You'll die.

1092
01:20:53,170 --> 01:20:55,170
Who do you think I am?

1093
01:21:11,170 --> 01:21:12,170
Oh... hey!

1094
01:21:19,670 --> 01:21:22,170
Hey! You're all dead!

1095
01:21:22,170 --> 01:21:24,670
Ugh... ow!

1096
01:21:24,670 --> 01:21:27,170
Ugh... what do I do?

1097
01:21:47,170 --> 01:21:49,170
She's pretty. Joey Wang.

1098
01:21:50,170 --> 01:21:51,170
Yeah.

1099
01:21:54,670 --> 01:21:57,670
There's no such girl in real life.

1100
01:21:59,670 --> 01:22:01,670
Who do you think is the prettiest?

1101
01:22:02,670 --> 01:22:08,460
Um... Joey Wang.

1102
01:22:08,670 --> 01:22:11,170
We said there's no such woman
in real life.

1103
01:22:11,670 --> 01:22:14,570
I've also fallen for another girl
at Jung Yi Performing Arts High School.

1104
01:22:15,170 --> 01:22:18,670
The girl with the short hair
with the pale face?

1105
01:22:18,670 --> 01:22:20,670
How did you guys know?

1106
01:22:20,670 --> 01:22:23,670
Everyone has a crush on her.

1107
01:22:23,670 --> 01:22:27,670
Then... there's another girl
that I've fallen for, in the study room.

1108
01:22:27,670 --> 01:22:29,170
She's a Third Year with long hair.

1109
01:22:29,170 --> 01:22:30,670
She goes to a performing arts school.

1110
01:22:30,670 --> 01:22:32,170
And wears a white cardigan, right?

1111
01:22:33,670 --> 01:22:38,670
You little punks...
you don't study but only ogle at girls?

1112
01:22:42,170 --> 01:22:44,170
Who else has a pretty face?

1113
01:22:45,170 --> 01:22:46,170
Also...

1114
01:22:46,170 --> 01:22:47,670
You have another one?

1115
01:22:50,270 --> 01:22:53,170
Doesn't it seem like Duk Seon has
gotten just a little bit cuter, lately?

1116
01:22:57,170 --> 01:22:58,170
Huh?

1117
01:22:58,170 --> 01:22:59,170
Yeah.

1118
01:23:00,670 --> 01:23:02,670
Yeah. A little.

1119
01:23:04,670 --> 01:23:07,170
Hey, Taek. What about you?

1120
01:23:10,170 --> 01:23:11,170
Yeah.

1121
01:23:12,670 --> 01:23:13,670
Hey, Jung Hwan.

1122
01:23:13,670 --> 01:23:15,670
You all must be crazy!

1123
01:23:15,670 --> 01:23:17,670
You're all out of your minds.

1124
01:23:17,670 --> 01:23:19,670
Are you all drunk?

1125
01:23:21,170 --> 01:23:22,170
Geez.

1126
01:23:23,170 --> 01:23:24,170
Geez.

1127
01:23:24,170 --> 01:23:26,170
You've all had too much.

1128
01:23:26,670 --> 01:23:28,670
Dammit! You farted!

1129
01:23:28,670 --> 01:23:29,670
Ew, it smells!

1130
01:23:29,670 --> 01:23:31,670
Stop that, already!

1131
01:23:31,670 --> 01:23:33,170
Why did you have to fart on us?

1132
01:23:34,170 --> 01:23:36,170
Damn it...

1133
01:24:00,170 --> 01:24:01,670
<i>[Sung Duk Seon]</i>

1134
01:24:02,170 --> 01:24:03,670
You read it, didn't you?

1135
01:24:03,670 --> 01:24:04,670
Read what?

1136
01:24:04,670 --> 01:24:06,170
My diary!

1137
01:24:06,170 --> 01:24:07,170
No.

1138
01:24:07,170 --> 01:24:08,670
Yeah, you did!

1139
01:24:08,670 --> 01:24:10,670
I told you, I didn't. Stop being so loud.

1140
01:24:10,670 --> 01:24:12,670
It's coming out of my mouth,
so mind your own!

1141
01:24:12,670 --> 01:24:13,670
Be quiet!

1142
01:24:13,670 --> 01:24:14,670
You read it, didn't you?

1143
01:24:14,670 --> 01:24:15,670
I told you, I didn't!

1144
01:24:15,670 --> 01:24:16,670
Mom!

1145
01:24:28,170 --> 01:24:29,170
You read it, didn't you?

1146
01:24:30,170 --> 01:24:32,170
Be quiet.

1147
01:24:32,170 --> 01:24:33,170
You did.

1148
01:24:33,170 --> 01:24:35,170
I told you, I didn't.

1149
01:24:43,670 --> 01:24:48,170
"At the hour when everything
is draped in darkness..."

1150
01:24:48,670 --> 01:24:52,170
"and therefore,
becomes a lonelier time..."

1151
01:24:52,670 --> 01:24:55,170
"at this time,
when the world is asleep..."

1152
01:24:55,170 --> 01:24:59,170
"my feelings for you cannot
seem to become still with the night."

1153
01:24:59,170 --> 01:25:00,670
I'm going to kill you! Hey!

1154
01:25:00,670 --> 01:25:02,670
<i>"They say that feelings
are for expressing."</i>

1155
01:25:02,670 --> 01:25:05,570
<i>"That's why I have to become brave
and let these words escape my lips..."</i>

1156
01:25:05,570 --> 01:25:06,670
Hey!

1157
01:25:06,670 --> 01:25:08,670
Mom! Duk Seon has someone she likes!

1158
01:25:08,670 --> 01:25:10,170
She even gave them chocolate!

1159
01:25:10,170 --> 01:25:11,670
Hey!

1160
01:25:18,670 --> 01:25:19,670
<i>[2015]</i>

1161
01:25:19,670 --> 01:25:21,870
How did I write these words
if I was sane at the time?

1162
01:25:23,170 --> 01:25:25,670
I want to throw it away,
but I don't know where I can.

1163
01:25:27,170 --> 01:25:29,670
I'm afraid to put it in the trash
in case someone finds it...

1164
01:25:31,670 --> 01:25:35,170
Oh my God... what nonsense.

1165
01:25:37,170 --> 01:25:39,170
You were a totally
rebellious kid back then.

1166
01:25:41,170 --> 01:25:43,670
Why did you spend time
with so many guys?

1167
01:25:47,170 --> 01:25:48,670
You read my diary, didn't you?

1168
01:25:51,170 --> 01:25:53,670
Wow. I can't believe you.

1169
01:25:53,670 --> 01:25:55,170
What the hell.

1170
01:25:56,170 --> 01:25:58,170
You read my diary, right?

1171
01:25:58,170 --> 01:26:01,170
- No.
- Yeah, you did!

1172
01:26:01,170 --> 01:26:02,170
I didn't.

1173
01:26:02,170 --> 01:26:05,170
Hey. Be honest with me.

1174
01:26:05,670 --> 01:26:08,170
How can you say "hey"
to your husband?

1175
01:26:08,170 --> 01:26:11,170
If you can say it,
why can't I?

1176
01:26:11,170 --> 01:26:12,670
You did read it, didn't you?

1177
01:26:12,670 --> 01:26:13,670
I didn't!

1178
01:26:20,170 --> 01:26:22,670
Who did you give the chocolate to?
It wasn't me.

1179
01:26:23,170 --> 01:26:24,170
Jesus...

1180
01:26:24,670 --> 01:26:27,170
Why did you read someone else's diary?

1181
01:26:27,170 --> 01:26:28,170
Huh? Why?

1182
01:26:28,170 --> 01:26:29,670
Who did you give it to?

1183
01:26:29,670 --> 01:26:31,170
I gave it to you!

1184
01:26:31,170 --> 01:26:32,170
You want to die?

1185
01:26:32,170 --> 01:26:33,170
It wasn't me!

1186
01:26:33,170 --> 01:26:34,170
Yeah, it was.

1187
01:26:34,170 --> 01:26:35,170
It wasn't you?

1188
01:26:37,670 --> 01:26:39,170
Yeah, it was.

1189
01:26:44,670 --> 01:26:46,670
I'll come back after a smoke.

1190
01:26:48,170 --> 01:26:49,670
It was you!

1191
01:26:49,670 --> 01:26:50,670
I told you, it wasn't me!

1192
01:27:02,670 --> 01:27:05,170
Geez... it was him.

1193
01:27:05,170 --> 01:27:08,170
It's been almost 30 years,
so I guess he forgot.

1194
01:27:08,670 --> 01:27:12,170
He was so smart back then, too.

1195
01:27:44,170 --> 01:27:45,170
<i>Jin Joo.</i>

1196
01:27:50,170 --> 01:27:51,170
<i>Does it taste good?</i>

1197
01:28:06,670 --> 01:28:07,670
<i>Where are you going?</i>

1198
01:28:07,670 --> 01:28:08,670
<i>To go eat ddukbokki!</i>

1199
01:28:18,670 --> 01:28:20,170
<i>Goodbye!</i>

1200
01:28:29,170 --> 01:28:31,670
<i>Your sister is going on
a field trip tomorrow!</i>

1201
01:28:36,170 --> 01:28:38,670
<i>I don't know!</i>

1202
01:28:43,670 --> 01:28:44,670
<i>Hey!</i>

1203
01:28:45,670 --> 01:28:47,670
<i>Hey!</i>

1204
01:28:55,670 --> 01:28:56,670
<i>Duk Seon.</i>

1205
01:28:56,670 --> 01:28:57,670
<i>Want to eat ramyun?</i>

1206
01:28:57,670 --> 01:28:59,670
<i>Duk Seon! Sung Duk Seon!</i>

1207
01:28:59,670 --> 01:29:00,670
<i>Duk Seon!</i>

1208
01:29:00,670 --> 01:29:01,770
<i>Sung Duk Seon!</i>

1209
01:29:01,770 --> 01:29:03,170
<i>Sun Woo is going to break the door.</i>

1210
01:29:03,170 --> 01:29:04,170
<i>Bye.</i>

1211
01:29:05,670 --> 01:29:07,170
<i>What are you going to do?</i>

1212
01:29:07,170 --> 01:29:08,170
<i>What?</i>

1213
01:29:08,170 --> 01:29:10,170
<i>It looks like he likes you.</i>

1214
01:29:14,670 --> 01:29:16,170
<i>Let's go, Sun Woo.</i>

1215
01:29:16,170 --> 01:29:21,170
Subtitles by DramaFever

